<subSubSection id="D8FB6574FFF5BD5F1F9CADAC932A0448" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="905E36FFFFF5BD5F1F9CADAC932A0448" blockId="10.[178,1085,1240,1320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">
Comparative notes: Aside from the male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="57E14D7CFFF5BD5F1B0AADAC9112046B" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orsunius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirgatus">
<emphasis id="A295EAEDFFF5BD5F1B0AADAC9112046B" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">O. flavovirgatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="57E14D7CFFF5BD5F1D72AD82932C046B" box="[604,777,1269,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orsunius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A295EAEDFFF5BD5F1D72AD82929C046B" box="[604,697,1270,1291]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">Orsunius</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
particularly by the coloration and by the distinctive punctation of the head and pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
